# Finishing a Development Branch
# Source: github.com/obra/superpowers | License: MIT

## When to Use
Use when development work is complete and ready for integration.
Triggers on: "I'm done", "finish the branch", "wrap up this feature",
"ready to merge", "close this PR". Also invoked at end of executing-plans.

---

## Step 1 — Verify Tests Pass

Before presenting ANY options:

```bash
npm test
npm run typecheck
npm run build
```

**If any fail:** Stop. Do not present integration options.
Report which checks failed and fix them first.

**Only proceed when all three pass.**

---

## Step 2 — Detect Workspace

```bash
# Check if in worktree
git rev-parse --git-dir
# .git → normal repo
# path ending in /worktrees/branch → worktree
```

---

## Step 3 — Present Options

### Normal repo or named-branch worktree (4 options):

```
All tests pass (N tests, 0 failures). What would you like to do?

1. Merge locally — merge this branch into main and clean up
2. Push + PR — push branch and create a GitHub PR
3. Keep branch — leave as-is, return to main
4. Discard — delete this work entirely
```

### Detached HEAD worktree (3 options):

```
All tests pass. What would you like to do?

1. Merge locally — squash changes into a commit on main
2. Push + PR — push as a new branch and create PR
3. Keep as-is — leave without committing
```

---

## Step 4 — Execute Choice

### Option 1 — Merge Locally
```bash
git checkout main
git merge feature/branch-name --no-ff -m "feat: description"
# Run tests on merged result
npm test
# Clean up worktree (only if created by superpowers)
git worktree remove .worktrees/branch-name  # if applicable
git branch -d feature/branch-name
```

### Option 2 — Push + PR
```bash
git push origin feature/branch-name
gh pr create --title "feat: description" --body "$(cat <<'EOF'
## Summary
- What was implemented

## Test plan
- [ ] All existing tests pass
- [ ] New tests cover the feature
- [ ] Verified locally

🤖 Generated with Claude Code
EOF
)"
```
**Do NOT remove worktree** — user needs it for PR iteration.

### Option 3 — Keep Branch
```bash
git checkout main
# Worktree stays intact
```

### Option 4 — Discard
**Require typed confirmation:**
```
This will permanently delete all changes on this branch.
Type "discard" to confirm:
```
After confirmation:
```bash
git checkout main
git worktree remove .worktrees/branch-name --force  # if worktree
git branch -D feature/branch-name
```

---

## Provenance Rule
Only remove worktrees that superpowers created:
- Located under `.worktrees/`
- Located under `worktrees/`
- Located under `~/.config/superpowers/worktrees/`

Never remove worktrees created outside superpowers.
